content.description: This is the low start to Placebo. Traverse the top of the lower boulder until you can make a huge span to the start of Placebo. Use heel-toe cams to work your hands along the jugs to a point where you can cut loose. Take the ride and finish up on Placebo.
content.location: Starts on the top-left corner of the lower boulder

content.description: Start hanging on a jug in the roof. Campus to another jug then do some crimping on a good heel to the top.
content.location: Starts on the lowest hold in the middle of the roof

content.description: Start at the base of the crack then hand jam and layback your way into the cave. Bit of a bad landing but really fun climbing.
content.location: The crack on the right side of the boulders

content.description: Start on rails and do a big move to the right facing break then traverse left on perpetually dirty slopers to where it's easiest to top out into the "gazebo". Right of the crack is not a part of the problem.
content.location: Right side of the boulder below Arecibo

content.description: Start hanging on a perfect sloper. Do some campus moves across more slopers into Placebo and finish the same.
content.location: Start hold is above the fallen tree on the left side of the top boulder

content.description: A satellite dish shaped boulder with another boulder beneath. There are a few problems along the lip of the roof and in the pit below. These boulders are near the edge of TVA land so be careful not to wander past the road nearby.
